connections and routes them to a .


Register this handler on a  to serve MSSQL
clients on the same port as HTTP, WebSocket, and SocketJack clients.



var mutable = new MutableTcpServer(1433, "MultiServer");
mutable.RegisterProtocol(new TdsProtocolHandler());
mutable.Listen();

Returns the appropriate stream for TDS I/O on this connection.
When TLS is active, returns the encrypted ;
otherwise returns the raw .

Fluent builder for generating .htaccess files that control directory
security and access when used with  or
.


Example usage:

server.Http.MapDirectory("/Update", updateDir, htaccess => {
    htaccess
        .DenyDirectoryListing()
        .AllowFrom("192.168.1.0/24")
        .DenyFiles("*.log", "*.bak")
        .RequireBasicAuth("Admin Area", "admin", "secret");
});

Imports schema and data from an existing MSSQL database into the
's in-memory store. A 
is automatically registered if one has not already been added.


var mutable = new MutableTcpServer(1433, "MultiServer");
mutable.Listen();

var conn = new SqlConnection("Server=.;Database=MyDb;Trusted_Connection=True;TrustServerCertificate=True;");
mutable.ImportFromMssql(conn);

